#git commands

->check version:- git --version
->configuration command:- git config --global user.name "user name"
                          git config --global user.email "email"

->to check config list:- git config --list

->intialise git in folder:- git init
->to add all changes to git :- git add .
->to add specific file cjhange:- git add file_name
->to commit the changes :- git commit -m"message"
->to push on github:- git push

->to know all about commits:- git log

->to checkout to specific commit:- git checkout commit_id


 


-> git stash :- 
-> git stash pop :- 
-> git restore filename :-
-> git restore --stages filename :-
-> git restore --soft HEAD~1 :-
-> git restore --hard HEAD~1 :-